description: On July 7th, the speed and adrenaline of professional cycling returns to the streets of San Rafael. Prepare yourself for the pageantry of the criterium style of racing -- short, fast, urban and gritty. Absorb the romanticism of a twilight race -- part fading sun, part Downtown Lights. This isn’t cycling you watch. This is cycling you feel.
course: The 1-km course, located in San Rafael’s vibrant downtown setting, starts and finishes on 4th Street while running clockwise on 4th, D St., 5th St., and A St. The Expo will occupy C St. between 4th & 5th St.
registration: All fields are limited and will sell-out. Please register early. No phone or faxed entries will be accepted.  All participants will sign a waiver/release form at registration. Those under 18 years old require a parent\'s or guardian\'s signature.  USA Cycling sanctioned. Riders must present a current USA Cycling license at registration. Competitor age is determined by the age of the rider on Dec. 31, 2012. Extra Race is $20. There are no refunds or transfers. If available, on-site registration will assess a $10 late fee.
notes: Neutral Technical support will be provided by SRAM.
directions: From US-101, take the Central San Rafael Exit, merge onto Irwin and make a left on 3rd St. The closed course is between Lootens & E St on 4th St.

San Diego Cup III
description:
Michelob Ultra San Diego Cup III

The Cup is back !!! 

Saturday August 18th, 5pm registration, 6 pm opening ceremonies, racing to follow shortly after. 

Third annual 3 race omnium event that features USAC racing (permit pending) in which individual racers earn points in each event for overall victory that night, USAC category upgrade points, and Saturday Night Lights series points. 

Addtionally, The Cup is a fun club challenge format where the club that earns the most points that night earns the right to hold The Cup for another year. There will be a 4000 meter team pursuit that will highlight the fastest riders of each club. 

A fine prize list from event title sponsor Michelob and Swamis Club sponsors Spy and Ride will make it a rewarding evening for all competitors as well! 

All racers will receive a San Diego Cup III poster !!!
registration: Online or at the track day of registration. If rider would like to enter an extra race, $5.00 additional.

title: UCSB Cowpie Classic Mountain Bike Race
Women's Team Pursuit Talent ID Camp
Back Abbey/Coates Cyclery Year End Training Ride
description: This is a non-competitive training ride for USCF licensed racers riding counter-clockwise around the \"Mini Hills\" loop. The event is intended for experienced riders and the pace will be moderate to fast with several moderate but short climbs. The ride will begin and end at the Coffee Bean on Indian Hill in Claremont. The course route may be changed at the start by the organizer due to weather, traffic or event turn out.
course: An approximately 30 mile loop through neighboring cities. Traffic should be light to moderate on secondary and primary roads with some sections requiring single file riding.
registration: Registration will be located in the open public area adjacent to the Coffee Bean, known as Smokers Alley\" on Indian Hill Ave. in downtown Claremont. Registration will be open from 6:45am to 7:00am.
notes: All USCF rules apply. Helmet’s are mandatory at all times while on your bike. Shirts must cover shoulders. No fixed gears. No tandems. Route is open to traffic and all traffic laws apply. Riders are responsible for their own safety with traffic and other bikes.
directions: From the East or West, exit at Towne Ave. off the 210 Fwy. Go South to Foothill Blvd. and turn left. Continue East until Indian Hill Ave and turn right. The ride will begin at the Coffee Bean on the West side of the road between W. Bonita Ave. and W. 2nd St.
